Form title: The Patient-Specific Functional Scale

Question Title: "Initial Assessment"
text: "I am going to ask you to identify up to three important activities that you are unable to do or are having difficulty
with as a result of your _________________ problem.  Today, are there any activities that you are unable to do
or having difficulty with because of your _________________ problem?"

Question Title: "Activities"
text: "Please name a specific activity that causes you pain. _______________"

Question Title: "Activities"
"text: Please rate your pain during this activity on the scale below."

Question Title: "Activities"
text: "Please name a specific activity that causes you pain. _______________"

Question Title: "Activities"
"text: Please rate your pain during this activity on the scale below."


Form title: "PFDI-20"

Question Title: "Instructions"
text: "Please answer all the questions in the following survey. These questions
will ask you if you have certain bladder, pelvic, or bowel symptoms and,
if you do, how much they bother you. Answer these questions by choosing the
appropriate number. While answering these questions, please consider your
symptoms over the last 3 months. All items use the following format with
a response scale from 0-4."

Question Title: "Pelvic Organ Prolapse Distress Inventory 6 (POPDI-6)"
text: "Do you usually experience pressure in the lower abdomen?"
(rate 0-4)

Question Title: "Colorectal-Anal Distress Inventory 9 (CRAD-8)"
text: "Do you feel you need to strain too hard to have a bowel movement?"
(rate 0-4)

Question Title: "Urinary Distress Inventory 6 (UDI-6)"
text: "Do you experience frequent urination?"
(rate 0-4)

Question Title: "Urinary Distress Inventory 6 (UDI-6)"
text: "Do you usually experience difficulty emptying your bladder?"
(rate 0-4)